g.text: A complete program (ProgramFile) consists of one or more program units.
There is exactly one main program which begins with a PROGRAM statement
This statement appears only at the beginning of the main program and the symbolic
name main-name must be unique (not used elsewhere in any of the program units).
There may also be any number of external procedures (functions and subroutines) and BLOCK DATA subprograms.
Every program unit must end with an END statement.
